    "{\"#\":432,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:35:58.588575Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqTagsPatch\":{\"id\":{\"gr\":80},\"patch\":{\"+\":[14],\"-\":[]}}}}",
    "{\"#\":433,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:36:23.488761Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqImplicationsPatch\":{\"dir\":\"<-\",\"id\":{\"gr\":80},\"patch\":{\"+\":[{\"gr\":5}],\"-\":[]}}}}",
    "{\"#\":434,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:37:14.199535Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":80},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Users will likely need to configure their own UC fields. This includes:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Removing fields.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Reordering fields.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Adding new fields.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Changing existing fields.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"This field set should apply to all UCs in the project.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"To be super-detailed, this \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"could\"}]},{\"lit\":\" be applied on a UC-by-UC basis, even more extreme would be UCs belonging to a given component get special fieldset modifications. But I think that's way too detailed.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"This affects the \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":6}},{\"lit\":\" feature. If a user decides they want an extra field for a subset of UCs, then unless functionality for that is provided, they will just add to all and either leave blank on irrelevant UCs, or fill with N/A. If they want to leave it empty then it may be considered a TODO within the \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":6}},{\"lit\":\" feature.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"When the user is configuring their fieldset, it should show them how many UCs are currently using a field and even show them the values. I might think “oh I don't use XXX, I'll just delete it”, where as I might be using it quite effectively in some UCs. Also do we hard delete their data? Maybe we should just soft delete and be able to swtich it on again later.\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":435,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:37:52.321177Z\",\"event\":{\"GenericReqCreate\":{\"reqId\":81,\"reqTypeId\":10,\"values\":[]}}}",
