    "{\"#\":439,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:41:08.617779Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":81},\"value\":[{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"You said previously “ I need […] organisation for other purposes”. What purposes can you think of? [Q is ambiguous]\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I can think of these purposes:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"BA filtering UC scope when reading/printing/reviewing UCs.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"A share filtering UC scope when being accessed by Readers.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"PM/BA determining the scope of their versions.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA accessing the influence/scope/size of an organisational unit. Inverse of 1.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Eg. How big is 1.0, how much work does Team A have to work with, what's completed.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Who is interested in those purposes and how important is it to them?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"1. BA. Very important as project grows. 10 Ucs = slightly important, 50 UCs important. 100+ UCs critical.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"BA & Readers. Same importance as above.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA/PM. Somewhat important.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"As above.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Why do those purposes matter?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"1. Near impossible to work without being to filter shit out.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"BA needs to manage amount of information washing over Reader. Also Reader, might not be privy to some requirements.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"PM/BA needs to estimate effort for Ucs in a version and balance it against time & cost.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA: Confirm allocations match what they've got in their head.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"PM: estimate effort/workload and balance it against external factors.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What would happen if you couldn't use the product to organise you Ucs in the groups?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"1. I would be very pissed off. I would have to use the editor to view each one-by-one. Wrt printing I'd just have to print everything and cross out certain UC titles.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"I would have to manually select Ucs. Every time a UC came in-scope or went out-of-scope I'd have to manually update all shares. Annoying.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"?\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Actually I misread. If the product didn't have any org features in it then I'd have only 2 options.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Use some external tool (Excel) to do the same thing. I'd have a row that matched the requirement Ids and then columns for the org stuff. That would be annoying because I would have to either omit titles from the external doc or copy titles into it and then they'd get out of sync.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I'd abuse the titles of Ucs to add extra information. Things like [VERSION: 1.0]. Things would get ugly.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If versions are metadata instead of real UC content, why do some people want them to look like they are part of the UC?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"• People are used to it. It's the way it's commonly done. Decades of precedent.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"The distinction between content and org metadata is fine and not commonly recognised.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"When sharing/reviewing a UC the Reader will often like to see associated org data.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Where else to put it?\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about groupings other than version, do they all have the same relationship to Ucs?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"Vague: Make relationships explicit.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What attributes do <grouping> have?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"See feature-organisation.ods.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If groupings were implemented without attributes, what problems would still exist, or arise?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Looking at the direct attributes, it wouldn't be a big deal. If everything had a single description attribute tht would probably be more than enough. If there were no attributes at all, I don't think it would matter too much.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"For relation-attributes however, \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"see feature-organisation.ods\"}]},{\"lit\":\".\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What will the consequences be if <each one> is missing from the app? In the UC publish view, how is <grouping> normally integrated? Why do readers of the doc need to see it?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"See feature-organisation.ods.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What's the trade-off between time and value?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Something must be done to solve the scope problem. Everything else is nice to have.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"The value should be sufficient to solve the scope problem with high value costing up to a month of time.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"How can we judge the success of this solution?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Have an unorganised project of approx 100 Ucs.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Organise all 100 in into 5 versions in under 10 minutes.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Have a version with 40 Ucs in it, redistribute every 5th UC in a different version in under 5 minutes. (eg. 20% to ver A, 20% to ver B, etc.)\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":440,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T02:41:20.089532Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":81},\"value\":[{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"You said previously “ I need […] organisation for other purposes”. What purposes can you think of? [Q is ambiguous]\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I can think of these purposes:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"BA filtering UC scope when reading/printing/reviewing UCs.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"A share filtering UC scope when being accessed by Readers.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"PM/BA determining the scope of their versions.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA accessing the influence/scope/size of an organisational unit. Inverse of 1.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Eg. How big is 1.0, how much work does Team A have to work with, what's completed.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Who is interested in those purposes and how important is it to them?\"}]},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"BA. Very important as project grows. 10 Ucs = slightly important, 50 UCs important. 100+ UCs critical.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA & Readers. Same importance as above.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA/PM. Somewhat important.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"As above.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Why do those purposes matter?\"}]},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Near impossible to work without being to filter shit out.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA needs to manage amount of information washing over Reader. Also Reader, might not be privy to some requirements.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"PM/BA needs to estimate effort for Ucs in a version and balance it against time & cost.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"BA: Confirm allocations match what they've got in their head.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"PM: estimate effort/workload and balance it against external factors.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What would happen if you couldn't use the product to organise you Ucs in the groups?\"}]},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"I would be very pissed off. I would have to use the editor to view each one-by-one. Wrt printing I'd just have to print everything and cross out certain UC titles.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I would have to manually select Ucs. Every time a UC came in-scope or went out-of-scope I'd have to manually update all shares. Annoying.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"?\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Actually I misread. If the product didn't have any org features in it then I'd have only 2 options.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Use some external tool (Excel) to do the same thing. I'd have a row that matched the requirement Ids and then columns for the org stuff. That would be annoying because I would have to either omit titles from the external doc or copy titles into it and then they'd get out of sync.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I'd abuse the titles of Ucs to add extra information. Things like [VERSION: 1.0]. Things would get ugly.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If versions are metadata instead of real UC content, why do some people want them to look like they are part of the UC?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"People are used to it. It's the way it's commonly done. Decades of precedent.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The distinction between content and org metadata is fine and not commonly recognised.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"When sharing/reviewing a UC the Reader will often like to see associated org data.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Where else to put it?\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about groupings other than version, do they all have the same relationship to Ucs?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"Vague: Make relationships explicit.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What attributes do <grouping> have?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"See feature-organisation.ods.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If groupings were implemented without attributes, what problems would still exist, or arise?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Looking at the direct attributes, it wouldn't be a big deal. If everything had a single description attribute tht would probably be more than enough. If there were no attributes at all, I don't think it would matter too much.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"For relation-attributes however, \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"see feature-organisation.ods\"}]},{\"lit\":\".\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What will the consequences be if <each one> is missing from the app? In the UC publish view, how is <grouping> normally integrated? Why do readers of the doc need to see it?\"}]},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"See feature-organisation.ods.\"}]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What's the trade-off between time and value?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Something must be done to solve the scope problem. Everything else is nice to have.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"The value should be sufficient to solve the scope problem with high value costing up to a month of time.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"How can we judge the success of this solution?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Have an unorganised project of approx 100 Ucs.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Organise all 100 in into 5 versions in under 10 minutes.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Have a version with 40 Ucs in it, redistribute every 5th UC in a different version in under 5 minutes. (eg. 20% to ver A, 20% to ver B, etc.)\"}]}}}",
