    "{\"#\":475,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:11:13.538839Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqImplicationsPatch\":{\"dir\":\"<-\",\"id\":{\"gr\":88},\"patch\":{\"+\":[{\"gr\":22}],\"-\":[]}}}}",
    "{\"#\":476,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:11:16.783260Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqTagsPatch\":{\"id\":{\"gr\":88},\"patch\":{\"+\":[14],\"-\":[]}}}}",
    "{\"#\":477,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:12:13.628804Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":88},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Let's see what types of high-level requirements there are.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"Business Objectives & Success Criteria\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Business Risks\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Major Features\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Exclusions & Limitations\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Assumptions & Dependencies\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Operating Environment\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Quality Attributes\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"So what are the differences between HL & LL requirements? I'm not really sure anymore. Maybe none... Some of them (SC, EX, LI, AS, DE) might be a bit ambiguous. How? Um, let's see...\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"SC: project/business vs functional/implementation\"}],[{\"lit\":\"EX: Project scope vs functional/implementation (?)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"LI: Project scope vs functional/implementation (?)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"AS: “\"}],[{\"lit\":\"DE: “\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Ok, it seems that SC is the only one that would matter and even then probably not much. Scope could be distinguished by grouping or if one really wanted, by creating different requirement-types.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Why are HL & LL distinguished then? I guess HL comes down from the Gods at the beginning of a project and isn't edited anywhere near as much as LL reqs are. In fact, I'd often not want to see HL reqs when I'm working on LL reqs. Vica-versa too; when I'm working on business/scope reqs and making project-wide considerations I don't want to see the fine-grained solution requirements.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Also there's overlap between this and \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":7}},{\"lit\":\" in which features are stored as groupings. What's missing between traditional MFs and the desired functionality in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":7}},{\"lit\":\" is nesting. (i.e. MFs normally don't list sub-features as children reqs... but they could/should!). Nesting sounds like it will come as part of \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":12}},{\"lit\":\" which means the missing link would be \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":13}},{\"lit\":\".\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":478,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:12:24.799259Z\",\"event\":{\"GenericReqCreate\":{\"reqId\":89,\"reqTypeId\":10,\"values\":[]}}}",
    "{\"#\":479,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:12:32.455717Z\",\"event\":{\"GenericReqTitleSet\":{\"id\":89,\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Issues: Q&A\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":480,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:16:52.848455Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":89},\"value\":[{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"When would you need to \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"see the total number\"}]},{\"lit\":\"_ of incompletions?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"When I'm gearing up to move on to the next phase, finish off a bunch of requirements, when I just want to know how close I am to completion...\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"When would you need to \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"filter the scope\"}]},{\"lit\":\" and then see the new total number of incompletions?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"When I want to finish off a subset of requirements. I might want to make sure all the requirements for phase 1 are complete, or maybe everything pertaining to 3 Major Features.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"When would you need to see a \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"list of UCs and the number of incompletions in each\"}]},{\"lit\":\"? If that feature were missing, when would you realise that it was missing? What would you do in that case?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"When I knew I had a bunch of incompletions outstanding and I wanted to\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"access their impact.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Example: if I see that 80% are in UC-3 which I don't care about right now, and see that UC-4 and UC-5 (both of which I want complete now) have 3 each.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"quickly understand why there are as many as there are.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Example: there are 10 total, I think whaaaaaaaat there should only be 2 or 3, I see a list of UCs with number of incompletions in each, the combination of UC title and incompetion count is enough to jog my memory and/or for me to understand the validity of the total number.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"I would realise the lack of this feature...\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"If I saw a total number and thought “really? why?” and couldn't see a breakdown.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If in the above scenario a few UCs had so many that they dominated the breakdown and have it hard to discern the 1 or 2 odd ones here-and-there that I was actually interested in.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If I were interested in the completion of a subset of UCs not easily specified by a filter.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"In that case I would...\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"spend more time and energy parsing the breakdown.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"spend more time and energy fucking around with filters.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"jump from UC to UC manually looking for completions.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"When editing a UC\"}]},{\"lit\":\", would you ever want to see the number of incompletions therein? If that feature were missing, when would you realise that it was missing? What would you do in that case?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I would want to know what was outstanding as incompetions. Seeing a single number somewhere on the screen would be one option, but then after seeing the number if it were non-zero I'd next want to find the incompletions themselves and probably edit them. If I were just expecting and looking for a zero, then cool. Presuming all incompletions are coloured red I would probably just quickly scan the screen for anything red.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Honestly I probably wouldn't realise the feature was missing. If I did, the UC would probably be massive, I'd be on a small screen with some shitty trackpad and even then I'd just blame the laptop. Ok, well if incompletions were not coloured red and didn't jump out at me, that's when I'd notice but then there'd be the problem of “ok, I see a number, now where are they?”.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What are some examples of \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"additional information\"}]},{\"lit\":\" that you would store with a \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"TODO\"}]},{\"lit\":\"?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Often nothing but when present, a free text explaination such as “Analyse further”, “Ambiguous”, “Unverified”, “Conflicts with [uc-6]”.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What are some examples of \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"additional information\"}]},{\"lit\":\" that you would store with a \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"TBD\"}]},{\"lit\":\"?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"“Waiting on Bob”, “Pending arch meeting”\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Why would you ever need to add \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"new incompletion types\"}]},{\"lit\":\"? How would you work without that ability?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"If there were a few common reasons for incompletion. “Ambiguous.” “Pending decision on A.B.C.”. Without that ability it would be super annoying to have to read every note attached to a TODO to determine it's underlying cause or classification. Things like ambiguity can usually be clarified anytime as they are an issue with language; a BA with free time would want to see those and filter out incompetions pending external information. On the other hand, if a specific decision is holding up many requirements, once that decision has been made a BA would want to see all incompetions that are waiting on it and resolve them all at once. Without custom incompetion types the BA'd have to read through everything which could make the incompetion summary useless; they might decide it would be less effort to go from memory to certain UCs they remember are related and manually scan for those specific incompetions there.\"},{\"h5\":[{\"lit\":\"What determines whether a UC \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"field is mandatory\"}]},{\"lit\":\"?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Company/project/team rules. Importance of a field.\"},{\"h5\":[{\"lit\":\"What can cause that decision to \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"change\"}]},{\"lit\":\"?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"The wind. It's fairly arbitrary. Just based on human minds which are fickle. Also a field can seem mandatory and then after writing a few UCs people change their minds.\"},{\"h5\":[{\"lit\":\"How often would you anticipate such a change?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"If it's an organisation-driven mandate, then it will occur rarely/occasionally. If the decision is being made by a smaller team or single person and/or the project/org is young, then it will likely change often.\"},{\"h5\":[{\"lit\":\"What are the consequences of a field being mandatory or not?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Mandatory fields should be monitored for emptiness. UCs shouldn't be marked as complete or forgotten when mandatory fields are blank. During review they are sought out and resolved.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If one were \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"editing UC fields\"}]},{\"lit\":\", would they ever need to \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"decide mandatory-ness\"}]},{\"lit\":\" at the same time? What would happen if they couldn't select mandatory-ness when editing fields?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Yes, I think they would. If I couldn't decide when adding a field, that would mean the system defaults it to either being mandatory or optional; if that default is ever not what I want them I'm going to find it annoying to have to go to another screen to check and modify that.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"If the system didn't provide the ability to record \"},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"loose notes\"}]},{\"lit\":\" as incompletions, what affect would that have on your requirements work? What are some examples of loose-note incompletions?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I'd have to…\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"maintain a separate list elsewhere. As a team of 1 I'd be fine with that, having a piece of paper and TODO list if it would be the full picture which it wouldn't be because the system would already be tracking a bunch of other incompletions. That would mean I'd have to look at my own list, and look at the screen, and mush them in my head. Also if I weren't working from home and didn't have my list of me I'd be unhappy.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"bastardise the system. I would start storing TODOs in inappropriate requirements just to have them tracked.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example loose-note incompetions:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"ABC is has gone out-of-scope. Revise all the XYZ stuff to remove references/considerations.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Consider custom fields for MF-[12]2.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Modify everything under MF-0[67] to apply to all kinds of reqs instead of just UCs.\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":481,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-02T03:17:00.052063Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqTagsPatch\":{\"id\":{\"gr\":89},\"patch\":{\"+\":[14],\"-\":[]}}}}",
