    "{\"#\":568,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-04T02:41:15.060968Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":102},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Deepti was entering requirements following Chen's process where you do interviews first, then create MFs after analysing them. In that case you have IV → MF but her IV's MF field was blank (and showing as an issue) because imp field calculation only considers backwards-implication, not forwards. Thinking about this it seems to make sense that forward-implication be considered too. The reason I'm not just gonna jump in and implement it is that I'm concerned about transitivity. Should it be transitive? Seems like it definitely should, but then what about large, complex trees? Will there be problems? Needs analysis.... And here we are.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be problems with transitive forward implication?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's just consider some scenarios:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" IV-1 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field\"}],[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → IV-2 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" As above, IV-2 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field, it seems logical that IV-1 should too. eg. \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"we need to solve X\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"here's how we can solve X, with MF-1!\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → MF-1\"}],[{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 --> IV1 --> UC1 --> IV2\"}},{\"lit\":\"and then\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB3 ---------------------------------------------------+\\n                                                       |\\nFB2 -------------------------------------------+       |\\n                                               ↓       ↓\\nFB1 --> IV1 --> UC1(DEAD) --> IV2 --> UC2 --> MF1 --> FR1\\n         |                     ↑       |\\n         +---------------------+       +----> MF2\"}},{\"lit\":\"With transitive forward-implication being considered we end up with\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"  FB1 - MF1,2\\n  FB2 - MF1\\n  FB3 - ∅. INTERESTING!! should be MF1 because FR1's MF is MF1 via backward-implication\\n  IV1 - MF1,2\\n  IV2 - MF1,2\\n  UC2 - MF1,2\\n  MF1 - should be off but if not, should only be self. DANGEROUS would be if MF-2 were included because UC2→MF1, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\\n  MF2 - should be off but if not, should only be self. DANGEROUS would be if MF-1 were included because UC2→MF2, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\"}}]]},{\"lit\":\"Shit, so that's interesting.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"transitive forward implication seems to be ok\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it doesn't seem to be enough in the case of FB3→FR1. What's the precise rule?\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":569,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-04T03:06:47.780113Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":102},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Deepti was entering requirements following Chen's process where you do interviews first, then create MFs after analysing them. In that case you have IV → MF but her IV's MF field was blank (and showing as an issue) because imp field calculation only considers backwards-implication, not forwards. Thinking about this it seems to make sense that forward-implication be considered too. The reason I'm not just gonna jump in and implement it is that I'm concerned about transitivity. Should it be transitive? Seems like it definitely should, but then what about large, complex trees? Will there be problems? Needs analysis.... And here we are.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be problems with transitive forward implication?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's just consider some scenarios:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" IV-1 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field\"}],[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → IV-2 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" As above, IV-2 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field, it seems logical that IV-1 should too. eg. \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"we need to solve X\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"here's how we can solve X, with MF-1!\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → MF-1\"}],[{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 --> IV1 --> UC1 --> IV2\"}},{\"lit\":\"and then\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"MF4\\n ↓\\nFB3 ---------------------------------------------------+\\n ↑                                                     |\\nFB4                                                    |\\n                                                       |\\nFB2 -------------------------------------------+       |\\n                                               ↓       ↓\\nFB1 --> IV1 --> UC1(DEAD) --> IV2 --> UC2 --> MF1 --> FR1\\n         |                     ↑       |\\n         +---------------------+       +----> MF2 --> MF3\\n           (manually relinked)\"}},{\"lit\":\"With transitive forward-implication being considered we end up with\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"    FB1 - MF1,2\\n    FB2 - MF1\\n    FB3 - MF4. INTERESTING!! should be MF1 also be included because FR-1's MF is MF1?\\n    FB4 - ∅.   INTERESTING!! should inherit FB3's MF field values\\n    IV1 - MF1,2\\n    IV2 - MF1,2\\n    UC2 - MF1,2\\n    MF1 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-2 were included because UC2→MF1, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\\n    MF2 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-1 were included because UC2→MF2, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\\n    MF3 - should be off but if not, should be self + MF2. DANGEROUS as above, shouldn't include MF1\\n    MF4 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-1 were included because of FR1\"}}]]},{\"lit\":\"Shit, so that's interesting.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"transitive forward implication seems to be ok\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it doesn't seem to be enough in the case of FB3→FR1.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Problems\"}]},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"the FB{3,4} case should consider values in the MF field of forward imps\"}],[{\"lit\":\"if MF1 → MF2 then it can't be a cycle\"}],[{\"lit\":\"MF1 shouldn't consider UC2's MF field (because it's backwards? or because subject is also MF?)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"should this be implemented universally or should there be some config in the imp field?\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What's the precise new rule?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Considerations:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"forward vs backward\"}],[{\"lit\":\"imp field vs imp tree\"}],[{\"lit\":\"req type = imp field type (at each decision point)\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"So if the imp field is MF...\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"all MFs in the subject's backward implication tree\"}],[{\"lit\":\"all MFs in the subject's forward implication tree, unless both subject & target are MF\"}],[{\"lit\":\"for each transitively forward-implied req, add the values of their MF fields\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":570,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-04T03:16:47.189848Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":102},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Deepti was entering requirements following Chen's process where you do interviews first, then create MFs after analysing them. In that case you have IV → MF but her IV's MF field was blank (and showing as an issue) because imp field calculation only considers backwards-implication, not forwards. Thinking about this it seems to make sense that forward-implication be considered too. The reason I'm not just gonna jump in and implement it is that I'm concerned about transitivity. Should it be transitive? Seems like it definitely should, but then what about large, complex trees? Will there be problems? Needs analysis.... And here we are.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be problems with transitive forward implication?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's just consider some scenarios:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" IV-1 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field\"}],[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → IV-2 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" As above, IV-2 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field, it seems logical that IV-1 should too. eg. \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"we need to solve X\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"here's how we can solve X, with MF-1!\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → MF-1\"}],[{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 --> IV1 --> UC1 --> IV2\"}},{\"lit\":\"and then\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"MF4\\n ↓\\nFB3 ---------------------------------------------------+\\n ↑                                                     |\\nFB4                                                    |\\n                                                       |\\nFB2 -------------------------------------------+       |\\n                                               ↓       ↓\\nFB1 --> IV1 --> UC1(DEAD) --> IV2 --> UC2 --> MF1 --> FR1\\n         |                     ↑       |\\n         +---------------------+       +----> MF2 --> MF3\\n           (manually relinked)\"}},{\"lit\":\"With transitive forward-implication being considered we end up with\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"    FB1 - MF1,2\\n    FB2 - MF1\\n    FB3 - MF4. INTERESTING!! should be MF1 also be included because FR-1's MF is MF1?\\n    FB4 - ∅.   INTERESTING!! should inherit FB3's MF field values\\n    IV1 - MF1,2\\n    IV2 - MF1,2\\n    UC2 - MF1,2\\n    MF1 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-2 were included because UC2→MF1, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\\n    MF2 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-1 were included because UC2→MF2, and UC2 has MF1,2 in it's MF field\\n    MF3 - should be off but if not, should be self + MF2. DANGEROUS as above, shouldn't include MF1\\n    MF4 - should be off but if not, should only be self.  DANGEROUS if MF-1 were included because of FR1\"}}]]},{\"lit\":\"Shit, so that's interesting.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"transitive forward implication seems to be ok\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it doesn't seem to be enough in the case of FB3→FR1.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Problems\"}]},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"the FB{3,4} cases should consider values in the MF field of forward imps\"}],[{\"lit\":\"if MF1 → MF2 then it can't be a cycle\"}],[{\"lit\":\"MF1 shouldn't consider UC2's MF field (because it's backwards? or because subject is also MF?)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"should this be implemented universally or should there be some config in the imp field?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"how will this affect the imp graph? everything relevant should be visible - i.e. if we're looking at FB3, it will show FR1, but it should also show MF1 (not UC2 though)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"the whole fucking thing about implication is that \"},{\"mono\":\"(A ⇒ B) ≠> (B ⇒ A)\"},{\"lit\":\" - FB3 implied FR1, maybe FR1 can exist without FB3. Why should FB3 inherit it's MF?\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What's the precise new rule?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's do it step by step...\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Firstly, what's the expectation?\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 - 1,2,3\\nFB2 - 1\\nFB3 - 4\\nFB4 - ∅\\nIV1 - 1,2\\nIV2 - 1,2\\nUC2 - 1,2\\nMF1 - 1\\nMF2 - 2\\nMF3 - 2,3\\nMF4 - 4\"}},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"all MFs in the subject's backward & forward implication tree\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 - 1,2\\nFB2 - 1\\nFB3 - 4\\nFB4 - ∅\\nIV1 - 1,2\\nIV2 - 1,2\\nUC2 - 1,2\\nMF1 - 1\\nMF2 - 2,3   ERROR: cycle\\nMF3 - 2,3   ERROR: cycle\\nMF4 - 4\"}}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":571,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-04T03:20:15.500030Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":102},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Deepti was entering requirements following Chen's process where you do interviews first, then create MFs after analysing them. In that case you have IV → MF but her IV's MF field was blank (and showing as an issue) because imp field calculation only considers backwards-implication, not forwards. Thinking about this it seems to make sense that forward-implication be considered too. The reason I'm not just gonna jump in and implement it is that I'm concerned about transitivity. Should it be transitive? Seems like it definitely should, but then what about large, complex trees? Will there be problems? Needs analysis.... And here we are.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be problems with transitive forward implication?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's just consider some scenarios:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" IV-1 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field\"}],[{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"IV-1 → IV-2 → MF-1:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" As above, IV-2 should definitely have MF-1 as in it's MF field, it seems logical that IV-1 should too. eg. \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"we need to solve X\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"\\\"here's how we can solve X, with MF-1!\\\"\"}]},{\"lit\":\" → MF-1\"}],[{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"FB1 --> IV1 --> UC1 --> IV2\"}},{\"lit\":\"and then\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"MF4\\n ↓\\nFB3 ---------------------------------------------------+\\n ↑                                                     |\\nFB4                                                    |\\n                                                       |\\nFB2 -------------------------------------------+       |\\n                                               ↓       ↓\\nFB1 --> IV1 --> UC1(DEAD) --> IV2 --> UC2 --> MF1 --> FR1\\n         |                     ↑       |\\n         +---------------------+       +----> MF2 --> M