    "{\"#\":676,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T06:27:34.060077Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":108},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"The need for this feature comes about pretty quickly once you've got more than a non-trivial amount of requirements in the system. When everything is in a flat list/grid, it's so hard to know what the hell is going on. I'm not gonna sit there and read everything (which means I'm not going to read anything cos understanding one line doesn't help me understand the est - it doesn't scale). I know for a fact that all of my content is hierarchical. Hierarchies are a great solution to this problem because it would allow me to look at the bunch of high-level stuff, and then drill into detail as I desire. So the abstract feature I need is comprised of the following:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"present a DAG/tree of content so that the DAG/tree structure is visible to the user\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow me to {collapse,expand} {single,multiple,all} rows in the req table\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow the DAG/tree structure to be configurable - eg. implication, req codes, statuses\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Status is an interesting one. I might want to view all my content grouped by MF and then status. Something like this:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+ MF-1\\n- MF-2\\n  + needs_analysis (4) (25%)\\n  - ready_for_dev (4) (25%)\\n    - FR-1\\n    - FR-8\\n    - FR-11\\n    - FR-13\\n  + implemented (8) (50%)\\n+ MF-3\\n+ MF-4\"}},{\"lit\":\"I don't know if this will overlap with \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":72}},{\"lit\":\" or not, but it would also be pretty nice if I could see the status breakdown in a single cell without having to expand the MFs. An idea could be just a coloured bar. Example:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+---+------+--------------------------+\\n| + | MF-1 | [###GREEN###|RED|#GRAY#] |\\n| + | MF-2 | [######GREEN######|RED#] |\\n| + | MF-3 | [GREEN|#####RED#####|GR] |\\n+---+------+--------------------------+\"}},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"So it looks like tags are like \"},{\"mono\":\"GROUP-BY\"},{\"lit\":\"s that can be nested.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Req codes are obvious (in isolation at least)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Implication tree is a must.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I just wonder about imp-field values (now that they're different from imp-tree). I think it's a \\\"must\\\" too. Actually they definitely are. If I'm interested in grouping by MF, I don't care how the implication was specified, I just want to see everything in that umbrella.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"ReqTable?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I'm pretty sure this should go into ReqTable.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"It's purpose is bulk / multiple reqs. This feature adheres to that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If I made a completely different screen I'd still want to have all of the req table functionality anyway (especially it's flexibility in letting me see specific aspects of reqs in bulk)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The view would have to be drastically different to justify adding a new screen. That means not a grid. Maybe there is some need for this but it would be insanity to only do that and not modify the ReqTable. It would mean users would find exactly what they're looking for on one screen and then have to manually try to reconstruct the same filter on the ReqTable. Yuk.\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":677,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T06:29:40.851489Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":108},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"The need for this feature comes about pretty quickly once you've got more than a non-trivial amount of requirements in the system. When everything is in a flat list/grid, it's so hard to know what the hell is going on. I'm not gonna sit there and read everything (which means I'm not going to read anything cos understanding one line doesn't help me understand the est - it doesn't scale). I know for a fact that all of my content is hierarchical. Hierarchies are a great solution to this problem because it would allow me to look at the bunch of high-level stuff, and then drill into detail as I desire. So the abstract feature I need is comprised of the following:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"present a DAG/tree of content so that the DAG/tree structure is visible to the user\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow me to {collapse,expand} {single,multiple,all} rows in the req table\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow the DAG/tree structure to be configurable - eg. implication, req codes, statuses\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Status is an interesting one. I might want to view all my content grouped by MF and then status. Something like this:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+ MF-1\\n- MF-2\\n  + needs_analysis (4) (25%)\\n  - ready_for_dev (4) (25%)\\n    - FR-1\\n    - FR-8\\n    - FR-11\\n    - FR-13\\n  + implemented (8) (50%)\\n+ MF-3\\n+ MF-4\"}},{\"lit\":\"I don't know if this will overlap with \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":72}},{\"lit\":\" or not, but it would also be pretty nice if I could see the status breakdown in a single cell without having to expand the MFs. An idea could be just a coloured bar. Example:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+---+------+--------------------------+\\n| + | MF-1 | [###GREEN###|RED|#GRAY#] |\\n| + | MF-2 | [######GREEN######|RED#] |\\n| + | MF-3 | [GREEN|#####RED#####|GR] |\\n+---+------+--------------------------+\"}},{\"lit\":\"So, it looks like:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"tags are like \"},{\"mono\":\"GROUP-BY\"},{\"lit\":\"s that can be nested\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Req codes are obvious (in isolation at least)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Implication tree is a must.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I just wonder about imp-field values (now that they're different from imp-tree). I think it's a \\\"must\\\" too. Actually they definitely are. If I'm interested in grouping by MF, I don't care how the implication was specified, I just want to see everything in that umbrella.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Tag groupings should be composable with imp-tree/field groupings (eg. version and then MF-tree)\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"ReqTable?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I'm pretty sure this should go into ReqTable.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"It's purpose is bulk / multiple reqs. This feature adheres to that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If I made a completely different screen I'd still want to have all of the req table functionality anyway (especially it's flexibility in letting me see specific aspects of reqs in bulk)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The view would have to be drastically different to justify adding a new screen. That means not a grid. Maybe there is some need for this but it would be insanity to only do that and not modify the ReqTable. It would mean users would find exactly what they're looking for on one screen and then have to manually try to reconstruct the same filter on the ReqTable. Yuk.\"}]]}]}}}",
