    "{\"#\":681,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T07:15:41.205793Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":108},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"The need for this feature comes about pretty quickly once you've got more than a non-trivial amount of requirements in the system. When everything is in a flat list/grid, it's so hard to know what the hell is going on. I'm not gonna sit there and read everything (which means I'm not going to read anything cos understanding one line doesn't help me understand the est - it doesn't scale). I know for a fact that all of my content is hierarchical. Hierarchies are a great solution to this problem because it would allow me to look at the bunch of high-level stuff, and then drill into detail as I desire. So the abstract feature I need is comprised of the following:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"present a DAG/tree of content so that the DAG/tree structure is visible to the user\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow me to {collapse,expand} {single,multiple,all} rows in the req table\"}],[{\"lit\":\"allow the DAG/tree structure to be configurable - eg. implication, req codes, statuses\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Status is an interesting one. I might want to view all my content grouped by MF and then status. Something like this:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+ MF-1\\n- MF-2\\n  + needs_analysis (4) (25%)\\n  - ready_for_dev (4) (25%)\\n    - FR-1\\n    - FR-8\\n    - FR-11\\n    - FR-13\\n  + implemented (8) (50%)\\n+ MF-3\\n+ MF-4\"}},{\"lit\":\"I don't know if this will overlap with \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":72}},{\"lit\":\" or not, but it would also be pretty nice if I could see the status breakdown in a single cell without having to expand the MFs. An idea could be just a coloured bar. Example:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"+---+------+--------------------------+\\n| + | MF-1 | [###GREEN###|RED|#GRAY#] |\\n| + | MF-2 | [######GREEN######|RED#] |\\n| + | MF-3 | [GREEN|#####RED#####|GR] |\\n+---+------+--------------------------+\"}},{\"lit\":\"So, it looks like:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"tags are like \"},{\"mono\":\"GROUP-BY\"},{\"lit\":\"s that can be nested\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Req codes are obvious (in isolation at least)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Implication tree is a must.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I just wonder about imp-field values (now that they're different from imp-tree). I think it's a \\\"must\\\" too. Actually they definitely are. If I'm interested in grouping by MF, I don't care how the implication was specified, I just want to see everything in that umbrella.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Tag groupings should be composable with imp-tree/field groupings (eg. version and then MF-tree)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Req types should be grouping criteria too\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"ReqTable?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"I'm pretty sure this should go into ReqTable.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"It's purpose is bulk / multiple reqs. This feature adheres to that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If I made a completely different screen I'd still want to have all of the req table functionality anyway (especially it's flexibility in letting me see specific aspects of reqs in bulk)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The view would have to be drastically different to justify adding a new screen. That means not a grid. Maybe there is some need for this but it would be insanity to only do that and not modify the ReqTable. It would mean users would find exactly what they're looking for on one screen and then have to manually try to reconstruct the same filter on the ReqTable. Yuk.\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":682,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T07:32:02.663135Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":109},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"It's the normal case that reqs are created, time passes, external work progresses, than somebody has to come back and update the tags.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"The first layer is just updating the FR's that I finished implementing. Normally not a big deal cos I also copy the IDs to my todo list. Still a bit annoying and there's \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":32}},{\"lit\":\" to address that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The next part is the most troublesome. Whatever reqs I just directly updated always have a big implication tree behind them. In order to keep all those reqs' status up-to-date, I have to manually access each one and update them.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"It's just not feasible.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"it's tedious\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's time-consuming\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I've forgotten a lot so I need to do lots of reading and thinking\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's error-prone -- so, so easy to make a mistake\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I often come back later to ShipReq to see (ask) what the current state is, not to tell it what it is\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Automating this would not only make users' lives so much easier, but be a significant selling point seeing as I don't know of anything else that does this.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"It'd have to be very flexible too. I guess there's a lot to work out because I have no idea how the solution's going to work. All I know is that I want to update a few leaf reqs, then look at the tree to see what effect it's had.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's think of a real workflow to see how I'd ideally use this.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Create MF (status defaults to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create implied IVs (their statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create next round of IVs (new IV statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark old IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"Create some FRs and SIs (new FRs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\", SIs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Repeat above with SIs until SIs are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I complete some FRs, moving them to \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I finish the last PRs\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}]}]]},{\"lit\":\"So thinking about what we need to implement this:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"there needs to be some configurable way of combining tags. Partial semigroup rules + defaulting to order = full semigroup and might be a great idea. Could even show the user a table of \"},{\"mono\":\"A |+| B = C\"}],[{\"lit\":\"this should be opt-in. Maybe per tag-field, or per tag?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Users should be able to copy/paste rules. Why? Smart/power users manually clicking around is one thing, but there might be a bunch of cases where you want to share config with someone or other projects of your own; users might want to backup their config.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in line with core ShipReq values, users need to be able to see a derived tag, and understand why that's the case. That means that even if we have a derived tag field with just a single value in it, users should be able to inspect it somehow (just hover?) and understand 1) that it was derived, 2) how it came to be, and 3) what the quantities were.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example of supp info:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"Content\\n  #a - 14 (FRs)\\n  #b -  6 (2 SIs, 4 FRs)\\n  #c -  1 (SI)\\n  #d -  1 (SI)\\n\\nCalculation\\n  = ((#a + #b) + #c) + #d\\n  = (#a + #c) + #d\\n  = #e + #d\\n  = #d\"}},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about...\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"deriving a multi-value result\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user input = allow and override | deny? configurable?\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":683,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T07:38:20.068098Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":109},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"It's the normal case that reqs are created, time passes, external work progresses, than somebody has to come back and update the tags.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"The first layer is just updating the FR's that I finished implementing. Normally not a big deal cos I also copy the IDs to my todo list. Still a bit annoying and there's \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":32}},{\"lit\":\" to address that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The next part is the most troublesome. Whatever reqs I just directly updated always have a big implication tree behind them. In order to keep all those reqs' status up-to-date, I have to manually access each one and update them.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"It's just not feasible.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"it's tedious\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's time-consuming\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I've forgotten a lot so I need to do lots of reading and thinking\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's error-prone -- so, so easy to make a mistake\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I often come back later to ShipReq to see (ask) what the current state is, not to tell it what it is\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Automating this would not only make users' lives so much easier, but be a significant selling point seeing as I don't know of anything else that does this.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"It'd have to be very flexible too. I guess there's a lot to work out because I have no idea how the solution's going to work. All I know is that I want to update a few leaf reqs, then look at the tree to see what effect it's had.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's think of a real workflow to see how I'd ideally use this.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Create MF (status defaults to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create implied IVs (their statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create next round of IVs (new IV statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark old IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"Create some FRs and SIs (new FRs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\", SIs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Repeat above with SIs until SIs are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I complete some FRs, moving them to \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I finish the last PRs\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}]}]]},{\"lit\":\"So thinking about what we need to implement this:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"there needs to be some configurable way of combining tags. Partial semigroup rules + defaulting to order = full semigroup and might be a great idea. Could even show the user a table of \"},{\"mono\":\"A |+| B = C\"},{\"lit\":\". \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"Note: semigroup must be commutative\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"this should be opt-in. Maybe per tag-field, or per tag?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Users should be able to copy/paste rules. Why? Smart/power users manually clicking around is one thing, but there might be a bunch of cases where you want to share config with someone or other projects of your own; users might want to backup their config.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in line with core ShipReq values, users need to be able to see a derived tag, and understand why that's the case. That means that even if we have a derived tag field with just a single value in it, users should be able to inspect it somehow (just hover?) and understand 1) that it was derived, 2) how it came to be, and 3) what the quantities were.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example of supp info:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"Content\\n  #a     - 14 (FRs)\\n  #b     -  6 (2 SIs, 4 FRs)\\n  #c     -  1 (SI)\\n  #d     -  1 (SI)\\n  no tag -  1 (SI)\\n\\nCalculation / Derivation\\n  = ((#a + #b) + #c) + #d\\n  = (#a + #c) + #d\\n  = #e + #d\\n  = #d\"}},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about...\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"children that have multiple values?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"deriving a multi-value result?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user input? Allow users to manually specify (i.e. override) or not? Or make configurable?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"handle empties? eg. allow a rule to say ∅ + * = ∅?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"derivation simply being a sum and displaying as a bar (like the eg in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":108}},{\"lit\":\" )\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":684,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T07:40:22.947731Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":109},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"It's the normal case that reqs are created, time passes, external work progresses, than somebody has to come back and update the tags.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"The first layer is just updating the FR's that I finished implementing. Normally not a big deal cos I also copy the IDs to my todo list. Still a bit annoying and there's \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":32}},{\"lit\":\" to address that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The next part is the most troublesome. Whatever reqs I just directly updated always have a big implication tree behind them. In order to keep all those reqs' status up-to-date, I have to manually access each one and update them.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"It's just not feasible.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"it's tedious\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's time-consuming\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I've forgotten a lot so I need to do lots of reading and thinking\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's error-prone -- so, so easy to make a mistake\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I often come back later to ShipReq to see (ask) what the current state is, not to tell it what it is\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Automating this would not only make users' lives so much easier, but be a significant selling point seeing as I don't know of anything else that does this.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"It'd have to be very flexible too. I guess there's a lot to work out because I have no idea how the solution's going to work. All I know is that I want to update a few leaf reqs, then look at the tree to see what effect it's had.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's think of a real workflow to see how I'd ideally use this.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Create MF (status defaults to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create implied IVs (their statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create next round of IVs (new IV statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark old IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"Create some FRs and SIs (new FRs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\", SIs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Repeat above with SIs until SIs are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I complete some FRs, moving them to \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I finish the last PRs\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}]}]]},{\"lit\":\"So thinking about what we need to implement this:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"there needs to be some configurable way of combining tags. Partial semigroup rules + defaulting to order = full semigroup and might be a great idea. Could even show the user a table of \"},{\"mono\":\"A |+| B = C\"},{\"lit\":\". \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"Note: semigroup must be commutative\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"this should be opt-in. Maybe per tag-field, or per tag?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Users should be able to copy/paste rules. Why? Smart/power users manually clicking around is one thing, but there might be a bunch of cases where you want to share config with someone or other projects of your own; users might want to backup their config.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in line with core ShipReq values, users need to be able to see a derived tag, and understand why that's the case. That means that even if we have a derived tag field with just a single value in it, users should be able to inspect it somehow (just hover?) and understand 1) that it was derived, 2) how it came to be, and 3) what the quantities were.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example of supp info:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"Content\\n  #a     - 14 (FRs)\\n  #b     -  6 (2 SIs, 4 FRs)\\n  #c     -  1 (SI)\\n  #d     -  1 (SI)\\n  no tag -  1 (SI)\\n\\nCalculation / Derivation\\n  = #a + (#b + (#c + #d))\\n  = #a + (#b + #d)\\n  = #a + #f\\n  = #d\"}},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about...\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"children that have multiple values?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"deriving a multi-value result?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user input? Allow users to manually specify (i.e. override) or not? Or make configurable?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"handle empties? eg. allow a rule to say ∅ + * = ∅?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"derivation simply being a sum and displaying as a bar (like the eg in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":108}},{\"lit\":\")\"}]]}]}}}",
