 or per tag?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Users should be able to copy/paste rules. Why? Smart/power users manually clicking around is one thing, but there might be a bunch of cases where you want to share config with someone or other projects of your own; users might want to backup their config.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in line with core ShipReq values, users need to be able to see a derived tag, and understand why that's the case. That means that even if we have a derived tag field with just a single value in it, users should be able to inspect it somehow (just hover?) and understand 1) that it was derived, 2) how it came to be, and 3) what the quantities were.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example of supp info:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"Content\\n  #a     - 14 (FRs)\\n  #b     -  6 (2 SIs, 4 FRs)\\n  #c     -  1 (SI)\\n  #d     -  1 (SI)\\n  no tag -  1 (SI)\\n\\nCalculation / Derivation\\n  = #a + (#b + (#c + #d))\\n  = #a + (#b + #d)\\n  = #a + #f\\n  = #d\"}},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow semigroup\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Note: a < b.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We don't need a = a in the list is the result should always be a.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We don't need a > b because we get that by changing it to b < a.\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"analysed       + implemented    = implemented\\nanalysed       + needs_analysis = needs_analysis\\nanalysed       + ready_for_dev  = ready_for_dev\\nanalysed       + rejected       = analysed\\nimplemented    + needs_analysis = needs_analysis\\nimplemented    + ready_for_dev  = ready_for_dev\\nimplemented    + rejected       = implemented\\nneeds_analysis + ready_for_dev  = needs_analysis\\nneeds_analysis + rejected       = needs_analysis\\nready_for_dev  + rejected       = ready_for_dev\"}},{\"lit\":\"Hmm I wonder what that looks like if I add a constraint that \"},{\"mono\":\"a + b = a \\\\/ b\"},{\"lit\":\" and express it a bit more concisely where we take the larger value\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"analysed       < implemented\\nanalysed       < needs_analysis\\nanalysed       < ready_for_dev\\nanalysed       > rejected\\nimplemented    < needs_analysis\\nimplemented    < ready_for_dev\\nimplemented    > rejected\\nneeds_analysis > ready_for_dev\\nneeds_analysis > rejected\\nready_for_dev  > rejected\"}},{\"lit\":\"Am I creating a poset? Refl & anti-symm hold. Transitivity?\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[],\"code\":\"digraph G {\\nrankdir=BT\\nedge [dir=back]\\n\\nneeds_analysis -> analysed\\nneeds_analysis -> implemented\\nneeds_analysis -> ready_for_dev\\nneeds_analysis -> rejected\\n\\nready_for_dev  -> analysed\\nready_for_dev  -> implemented\\nready_for_dev  -> rejected\\n\\nimplemented    -> analysed\\nimplemented    -> rejected\\n\\nanalysed       -> rejected\\n\\n// 1. needs_analysis -> *\\n// 2. ready_for_dev  -> *\\n// 3. implemented    -> *\\n// 4. analysed       -> *\\n// 5. rejected       -> *\\n}\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"System needs to alert user to what's missing in their list and (if there is default handling) show them the default results.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about...\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"children that have multiple values?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"deriving a multi-value result?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user input? Allow users to manually specify (i.e. override) or not? Or make configurable?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"handle empties? eg. allow a rule to say ∅ + * = ∅?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"derivation simply being a sum and displaying as a bar (like the eg in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":108}},{\"lit\":\")\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Multi-value results\"}]},{\"lit\":\"There might be very legitimate cases where you want the result to be multiple values. Maybe something like \"},{\"mono\":\"#in_testing #pending_security_review\"},{\"lit\":\". An easy modification to the above would be to allow partial semigroup rules, and if a rule for x and y doesn't exist, then the result is simply \"},{\"mono\":\"#x #y\"},{\"lit\":\" (i.e. \"},{\"mono\":\"#x + #y\"},{\"lit\":\" implicitly / by-default \"},{\"mono\":\"= #x #y\"},{\"lit\":\").\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"I wonder how generalised that concept is? \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Set[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? If it were that flexible you'd need to prove infinite loops aren't possible.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"What about \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Option[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? That would allow tags to vanish from calculation which seems bizarre.\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":687,\"createdAt\":\"2020-07-16T08:44:21.665878Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":109},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"It's the normal case that reqs are created, time passes, external work progresses, than somebody has to come back and update the tags.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"The first layer is just updating the FR's that I finished implementing. Normally not a big deal cos I also copy the IDs to my todo list. Still a bit annoying and there's \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":32}},{\"lit\":\" to address that.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"The next part is the most troublesome. Whatever reqs I just directly updated always have a big implication tree behind them. In order to keep all those reqs' status up-to-date, I have to manually access each one and update them.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"It's just not feasible.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"it's tedious\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's time-consuming\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I've forgotten a lot so I need to do lots of reading and thinking\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's error-prone -- so, so easy to make a mistake\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I often come back later to ShipReq to see (ask) what the current state is, not to tell it what it is\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Automating this would not only make users' lives so much easier, but be a significant selling point seeing as I don't know of anything else that does this.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"It'd have to be very flexible too. I guess there's a lot to work out because I have no idea how the solution's going to work. All I know is that I want to update a few leaf reqs, then look at the tree to see what effect it's had.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Let's think of a real workflow to see how I'd ideally use this.\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Create MF (status defaults to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create implied IVs (their statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Create next round of IVs (new IV statuses default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark old IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"Create some FRs and SIs (new FRs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\", SIs default to \"},{\"mono\":\"needs_analysis\"},{\"lit\":\", I manually mark IV's as \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Repeat above with SIs until SIs are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I complete some FRs, moving them to \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"ready_for_dev\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"I finish the last PRs\"}],[{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"At this point, all children are either \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"},{\"lit\":\", \"},{\"mono\":\"rejected\"},{\"lit\":\" or \"},{\"mono\":\"analysed\"},{\"lit\":\". MF status should be \"},{\"mono\":\"implemented\"}]}]]},{\"lit\":\"So thinking about what we need to implement this:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"there needs to be some configurable way of combining tags. Partial semigroup rules + defaulting to order = full semigroup and might be a great idea. Could even show the user a table of \"},{\"mono\":\"A |+| B = C\"},{\"lit\":\". \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"Note: semigroup must be commutative\"}]}],[{\"lit\":\"this should be opt-in. Maybe per tag-field, or per tag?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Users should be able to copy/paste rules. Why? Smart/power users manually clicking around is one thing, but there might be a bunch of cases where you want to share config with someone or other projects of your own; users might want to backup their config.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in line with core ShipReq values, users need to be able to see a derived tag, and understand why that's the case. That means that even if we have a derived tag field with just a single value in it, users should be able to inspect it somehow (just hover?) and understand 1) that it was derived, 2) how it came to be, and 3) what the quantities were.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Example of supp info:\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"Content\\n  #a     - 14 (FRs)\\n  #b     -  6 (2 SIs, 4 FRs)\\n  #c     -  1 (SI)\\n  #d     -  1 (SI)\\n  no tag -  1 (SI)\\n\\nCalculation / Derivation\\n  = #a + (#b + (#c + #d))\\n  = #a + (#b + #d)\\n  = #a + #f\\n  = #d\"}},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Workflow semigroup\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Note: a < b.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We don't need a = a in the list is the result should always be a.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We don't need a > b because we get that by changing it to b < a.\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"analysed       + implemented    = implemented\\nanalysed       + needs_analysis = needs_analysis\\nanalysed       + ready_for_dev  = ready_for_dev\\nanalysed       + rejected       = analysed\\nimplemented    + needs_analysis = needs_analysis\\nimplemented    + ready_for_dev  = ready_for_dev\\nimplemented    + rejected       = implemented\\nneeds_analysis + ready_for_dev  = needs_analysis\\nneeds_analysis + rejected       = needs_analysis\\nready_for_dev  + rejected       = ready_for_dev\"}},{\"lit\":\"Hmm I wonder what that looks like if I add a constraint that \"},{\"mono\":\"a + b = a \\\\/ b\"},{\"lit\":\" and express it a bit more concisely where we take the larger value\"},{\"cb\":{\"code\":\"analysed       < implemented\\nanalysed       < needs_analysis\\nanalysed       < ready_for_dev\\nanalysed       > rejected\\nimplemented    < needs_analysis\\nimplemented    < ready_for_dev\\nimplemented    > rejected\\nneeds_analysis > ready_for_dev\\nneeds_analysis > rejected\\nready_for_dev  > rejected\"}},{\"lit\":\"Am I creating a poset? Refl & anti-symm hold. Transitivity?\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[],\"code\":\"digraph G {\\nrankdir=BT\\nedge [dir=back]\\n\\nneeds_analysis -> analysed\\nneeds_analysis -> implemented\\nneeds_analysis -> ready_for_dev\\nneeds_analysis -> rejected\\n\\nready_for_dev  -> analysed\\nready_for_dev  -> implemented\\nready_for_dev  -> rejected\\n\\nimplemented    -> analysed\\nimplemented    -> rejected\\n\\nanalysed       -> rejected\\n\\n// 1. needs_analysis -> *\\n// 2. ready_for_dev  -> *\\n// 3. implemented    -> *\\n// 4. analysed       -> *\\n// 5. rejected       -> *\\n}\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"System needs to alert user to what's missing in their list and (if there is default handling) show them the default results.\"},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"What about...\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"children that have multiple values?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"deriving a multi-value result?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user input? Allow users to manually specify (i.e. override) or not? Or make configurable?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"handle empties? eg. allow a rule to say ∅ + * = ∅?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"derivation simply being a sum and displaying as a bar (like the eg in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":108}},{\"lit\":\")\"}],[{\"lit\":\"a single field definition resulting in two virtual fields, one with the values, and another with composite-colour-bars? It's really a \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"view\"}]},{\"lit\":\" change, with the same content and even conceptual field. How can users change the way they want to view the same cell? Maybe add a little config with checkboxes like \\\"show percentage bars\\\" in the req table? But then what about req detail? It definitely shouldn't be part of the field's config.\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Multi-value results\"}]},{\"lit\":\"There might be very legitimate cases where you want the result to be multiple values. Maybe something like \"},{\"mono\":\"#in_testing #pending_security_review\"},{\"lit\":\". An easy modification to the above would be to allow partial semigroup rules, and if a rule for x and y doesn't exist, then the result is simply \"},{\"mono\":\"#x #y\"},{\"lit\":\" (i.e. \"},{\"mono\":\"#x + #y\"},{\"lit\":\" implicitly / by-default \"},{\"mono\":\"= #x #y\"},{\"lit\":\").\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"I wonder how generalised that concept is? \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Set[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? If it were that flexible you'd need to prove infinite loops aren't possible.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"What about \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Option[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? That would allow tags to vanish from calculation which seems bizarre.\"}]}}}",
