 you can single-click the field to toggle through view styles?\"}]]},{\"h4\":[{\"lit\":\"Multi-value results\"}]},{\"lit\":\"There might be very legitimate cases where you want the result to be multiple values. Maybe something like \"},{\"mono\":\"#in_testing #pending_security_review\"},{\"lit\":\". An easy modification to the above would be to allow partial semigroup rules, and if a rule for x and y doesn't exist, then the result is simply \"},{\"mono\":\"#x #y\"},{\"lit\":\" (i.e. \"},{\"mono\":\"#x + #y\"},{\"lit\":\" implicitly / by-default \"},{\"mono\":\"= #x #y\"},{\"lit\":\").\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"I wonder how generalised that concept is? \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Set[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? If it were that flexible you'd need to prove infinite loops aren't possible.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"What about \"},{\"mono\":\"A + A = Option[A]\"},{\"lit\":\"? That would allow tags to vanish from calculation which seems bizarre.\"}]}}}",
