"<blank>\"},{\"lit\":\" beside the derived tag. It wouldn't show up on the Issues page though so that could be confusing.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Seeing as simplicity and consistency from a user's point of view are core business goals, I guess we should accept (1) and (2) above, and reject (3) and (4).\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Yeah cool, done.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should happen when a child has multiple tags?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Simple. Treat them the same as we'd treat combining tags from multiple reqs that have a single tag each.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Shouldn't be any different.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"We've studied derivative statuses, what about versions?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Versions are interesting because they kind of go in the opposite direction as statuses.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"The simplest case:\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"FB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"If I tag MF1 as v1, I'd expect it to propagate down\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be any confusion / ambiguity / difficulty in the intersection between derived tags, and default tags?\"}]},{\"issue\":{\"desc\":[],\"type\":1}},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"It might be an idea to visually mark synthetic tags so that they're distinguishable from manually-assigned tags.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should we show, where?\"}]},{\"issue\":{\"desc\":[],\"type\":1}},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"reqtable vs req detail\"}],[{\"lit\":\"subject tag field vs anything else?\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"In req detail (at least), it would be cool to display the final tag value, and then next to it, a colour bar indicating the makeup.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Req table is a different kettle of fish because conciseness matters.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Hell we could even use the cell \"},{\"mono\":\"bottom-border\"},{\"lit\":\" to render the bar without padding. That's pretty concise.\"}]}}}",
