    "{\"#\":770,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-05T02:27:33.627937Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":117},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Versions are interesting because they kind of go in the opposite direction as statuses.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Consider this case:\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"node[style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#eeeeee\\\"]\\nMF1 [fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\" label=\\\"MF1\\\\n(v2)\\\"]\\nFR1 [fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\" label=\\\"FR1\\\\n(v1)\\\"]\\nFR4 [fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\" label=\\\"FR4\\\\n(v1)\\\"]\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"First of all,\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"If I removed v2 from MF1, I'd expect the whole graph to be v1\"}],[{\"lit\":\"If I removed v1 from FR1, I'd expect the whole graph to be v2\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Where as we've got a few options with this feature...\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"Bidirectional propagation (merge with manual)\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"FB1,MF1,IV1,FR1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV2,FR2,FR3 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV3,FR4 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\n\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"What's really interesting about this is that we combine manual values with derived values.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Bidirectional propagation (manual trumps)\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"FB1,MF1 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\"]\\nFR1,FR4 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\"]\\nIV1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\nFR2,IV2,FR3 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV3 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\n\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}}],[{\"lit\":\"Backwards-only propagation (merge with manual)\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"IV1,FR1,FR4 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\"]\\nFB1,MF1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV2\\nIV3 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\"]\\n\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}}],[{\"lit\":\"Forwards-only propagation (merge with manual)\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"FR1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\nMF1,IV1,IV2,FR2,FR3,IV3,FR4 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\"]\\n\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}}]]},{\"lit\":\"Unidirectionalism clearly doesn't work, so it's a toss-up between (1) and (2).\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"The questions come down to:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"Should FR1 inherit the v2 tag? No. I'm telling you this is coming in v1.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Should MF1 inherit the v1 tag? Yes. It's being delivered in both v1 & v2.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Should FB1 inherit the v1 tag? Yes. We've no way of knowing what info in FB1 is relevant to the v1 part of MF1, or the v2 part of MF1.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Hmmm so we actually want a different solution from the four above, one that looks like this:\"},{\"cb\":{\"attr\":[\"render\"],\"code\":\"FR1,FR4 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff\\\" penwidth=3]\\nMF1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\" penwidth=3]\\nFB1,IV1 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV2,FR2,FR3 [style=filled fillcolor=\\\"#99ff00\\\"]\\nIV3 [style=wedged fillcolor=\\\"#ddaaff:#99ff00\\\"]\\n\\nFB1 -> MF1 -> IV1 -> FR1,FR2\\nMF1 -> IV2 -> FR3\\nMF1 -> IV3 -> FR4\",\"lang\":\"dot\"}},{\"lit\":\"So the rule seems to be:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"Backwards propagation merges with manual, forwards propagation halts at manual\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":771,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-05T02:28:31.756215Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":114},\"value\":[{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"How can we judge the success of the solution?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"For \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"status tags\"}]},{\"lit\":\": this will be successful if I can use ShipReq as I have been, but with the following differences:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"when I finish an implementation task, I shouldn't need to update anything else\"}],[{\"lit\":\"when I mark a req as analysed, I shouldn't need to update anything else\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I should always be able to look at an MF's status to comprehend it's collective state (and obviously that data should be correct).\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"For \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"versions\"}]},{\"lit\":\", I basically only want to set them on MFs, and have them automatically propagate to everything else.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"For any derived tag I need to be able to quickly comprehend why the resulting value was derived.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Can you think of any unexpected or adverse consequences this could cause?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"It could be confusing if a req has a manually-assigned status tag but you're expecting it to auto-update\"}],[{\"lit\":\"It increases complexity when a users add new tags\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Are there any constraints or rules to which the feature must conform?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Apart from what was outlined in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":109}},{\"lit\":\" , no.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"There are constraints imposed by ShipReq's core business goals like comprehensibility, and simplicity. But the fact that we'll always explain how derived tags came to be, should address this. Not sure anything else is needed.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Which aspects of the feature are most critical to creating business value?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"automation\"}],[{\"lit\":\"reliability / correctness\"}],[{\"lit\":\"explanation / provenance\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What aspect of the feature most excites you?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"How much time & effort it will save me from having to manually keep everything up to date\"}],[{\"lit\":\"How much confusion it will save me / how much it will clarify my own mountain of content\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Should we have multiple weighted values instead of a consolidation?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"So instead of (18 completed + 1 ready_for_dev = ready_for_dev), what would it be like to just retain (18 completed + 1 ready_for_dev) as the value? Well for starters, the req would effectively have both tags (completed, ready_for_dev). Bubbling this up to the top you'd end up with MF's having nearly all the tags which seems like it'd be useless. I think just choosing one tag and displaying the breakdown/calculation is the way to go.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Apart from it being informational, what else would it affect? It would affect filtering. So filtering by rejected would now include all the non-rejected MFs and a bunch of intermediate (possibly valid) intermediate reqs too. That sounds like shit.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"I think it's a clear \\\"no\\\".\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Don't forget that when a semigroup rule for two values doesn't exist, we simply take both without consolidation. That's orthogonal to this question and decision.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should happen when there's no tag in a child?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Some possibilities:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"it doesn't affect the tag selection, but it does affect the explanation & percentage bar.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"they could be identified by making the tag field mandatory - then it'll appear in ones Issues\"}],[{\"lit\":\"we could just abort and propagate emptiness all the way up - that way it's clear that there's an error. On the other hand, now you'll see entire tree branches show up on the issues page, with it being unclear which req is the core req needing to be fixed\"}],[{\"lit\":\"we could also kind of cheat and display \"},{\"mono\":\"<blank>\"},{\"lit\":\" beside the derived tag. It wouldn't show up on the Issues page though so that could be confusing.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Seeing as simplicity and consistency from a user's point of view are core business goals, I guess we should accept (1) and (2) above, and reject (3) and (4).\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Yeah cool, done.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should happen when a child has multiple tags?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Simple. Treat them the same as we'd treat combining tags from multiple reqs that have a single tag each.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Shouldn't be any different.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"How will versions be derived?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Possibilities:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"req\":{\"gr\":117}}]]}]}}}",
