    "{\"#\":817,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-05T05:04:29.033990Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":114},\"value\":[{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"How can we judge the success of the solution?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"For \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"status tags\"}]},{\"lit\":\": this will be successful if I can use ShipReq as I have been, but with the following differences:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"when I finish an implementation task, I shouldn't need to update anything else\"}],[{\"lit\":\"when I mark a req as analysed, I shouldn't need to update anything else\"}],[{\"lit\":\"I should always be able to look at an MF's status to comprehend it's collective state (and obviously that data should be correct).\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"For \"},{\"**\":[{\"lit\":\"versions\"}]},{\"lit\":\", I basically only want to set them on MFs, and have them automatically propagate to everything else.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"For any derived tag I need to be able to quickly comprehend why the resulting value was derived.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Can you think of any unexpected or adverse consequences this could cause?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"It could be confusing if a req has a manually-assigned status tag but you're expecting it to auto-update\"}],[{\"lit\":\"It increases complexity when a users add new tags\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Are there any constraints or rules to which the feature must conform?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Apart from what was outlined in \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":109}},{\"lit\":\" , no.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"There are constraints imposed by ShipReq's core business goals like comprehensibility, and simplicity. But the fact that we'll always explain how derived tags came to be, should address this. Not sure anything else is needed.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Which aspects of the feature are most critical to creating business value?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"automation\"}],[{\"lit\":\"reliability / correctness\"}],[{\"lit\":\"explanation / provenance\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What aspect of the feature most excites you?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"How much time & effort it will save me from having to manually keep everything up to date\"}],[{\"lit\":\"How much confusion it will save me / how much it will clarify my own mountain of content\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Should we have multiple weighted values instead of a consolidation?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"So instead of (18 completed + 1 ready_for_dev = ready_for_dev), what would it be like to just retain (18 completed + 1 ready_for_dev) as the value? Well for starters, the req would effectively have both tags (completed, ready_for_dev). Bubbling this up to the top you'd end up with MF's having nearly all the tags which seems like it'd be useless. I think just choosing one tag and displaying the breakdown/calculation is the way to go.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Apart from it being informational, what else would it affect? It would affect filtering. So filtering by rejected would now include all the non-rejected MFs and a bunch of intermediate (possibly valid) intermediate reqs too. That sounds like shit.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"I think it's a clear \\\"no\\\".\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Don't forget that when a semigroup rule for two values doesn't exist, we simply take both without consolidation. That's orthogonal to this question and decision.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should happen when there's no tag in a child?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Some possibilities:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"it doesn't affect the tag selection, but it does affect the explanation & percentage bar.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"they could be identified by making the tag field mandatory - then it'll appear in one's Issues\"}],[{\"lit\":\"we could just abort and propagate emptiness all the way up - that way it's clear that there's an error. On the other hand, now you'll see entire tree branches show up on the issues page, with it being unclear which req is the core req needing to be fixed\"}],[{\"lit\":\"we could also kind of cheat and display \"},{\"mono\":\"<blank>\"},{\"lit\":\" beside the derived tag. It wouldn't show up on the Issues page though so that could be confusing.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Seeing as simplicity and consistency from a user's point of view are core business goals, I guess we should accept (1) and (2) above, and reject (3) and (4).\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Yeah cool, done.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should happen when a child has multiple tags?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Simple. Treat them the same as we'd treat combining tags from multiple reqs that have a single tag each.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"Shouldn't be any different.\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"How will status be derived?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Possibilities:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"req\":{\"gr\":116}}],[{\"req\":{\"gr\":118}}],[{\"req\":{\"gr\":119}},{\"lit\":\" <-- winner\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"The only difference between \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":116}},{\"lit\":\" & \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":118}},{\"lit\":\" is whether manual assignments remain; all derivations are the same. So let's think about the differences.\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"looking at an interview - you don't know whether it's fully implemented or not. Users might resort to later, clearing out the status so that it's derived. That would be terrible, because the user still has to go around modifying intermediate nodes. That's against the goal\"}],[{\"lit\":\"how would filters be affected? From a filter's point of view, I'd probably expect it to match against both the manual assignment and the override. Specifically, if I filter by analysed interviews, I should still see them all, even though they've been overridden by things like \"},{\"mono\":\"#implemented\"},{\"lit\":\". And if I filtered interviews by \"},{\"mono\":\"#implemented\"},{\"lit\":\" I would of course still expect them all to appear; to not do that would be crazy.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Ok that settles it. \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":116}},{\"lit\":\" is the winner.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"__\":[{\"lit\":\"Update:\"}]},{\"lit\":\" I've just added \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":119}},{\"lit\":\" which adds a derivative tag to a manual assignment and it's \"},{\"//\":[{\"lit\":\"much\"}]},{\"lit\":\" better!\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"filtering works as expected without any changes\"}],[{\"lit\":\"it's clearer in that if a user adds a manual tag, you see it\"}],[{\"lit\":\"user's gain control in that if a user adds a manual tag, it's there; it's not overridden\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"How will versions be derived?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"See \"},{\"req\":{\"gr\":117}},{\"lit\":\".\"},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"Will there be any confusion / ambiguity / difficulty in the intersection between derived tags, and default tags?\"}]},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"I think not so long as we always expose the provenance in a simply-comprehensible manner\"}],[{\"lit\":\"It might be an idea to visually mark synthetic tags so that they're distinguishable from manually-assigned tags.\"}]]},{\"h2\":[{\"lit\":\"What should we show, where?\"}]},{\"lit\":\"Where =\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"{ReqTable, ReqDetail}\"}],[{\"lit\":\"{subject tag field, All Tags}\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Decisions:\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"derivative tags should only be applied to tag fields, not tags in the [Other Tags] field\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in ReqDetail, it would be cool to display the final tag value, and then next to it, a colour bar indicating the makeup.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"in ReqTable, it would be cool to display a colour bar indicating the makeup as the cell bottom border\"}],[{\"lit\":\"All Tags just gets all the tags as normal\"}]]}]}}}",
