    "{\"#\":881,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:21:50.875857Z\",\"event\":{\"GenericReqCreate\":{\"reqId\":135,\"reqTypeId\":6,\"values\":[]}}}",
    "{\"#\":882,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:22:16.599114Z\",\"event\":{\"GenericReqTitleSet\":{\"id\":135,\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Never lose data before it's committed\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":883,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:22:57.517273Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":6,\"id\":{\"gr\":135},\"value\":[{\"lit\":\"Ólafur Páll Geirsson\"}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":884,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:27:58.113221Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":135},\"value\":[{\"web\":\"https://twitter.com/olafurpg/status/1295766220369788929\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"> I pressed escape and Jira just discarded my comment that I had been drafting for 30 minutes\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"> I wonder if there’s an extension that stores all text inputs in local storage for recovery. It’s hard to know in advance when you’re about to start drafting a long response.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We should do better. Maybe drafts should be stored in local storage until committed. In fact, what about this:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"User writes lots of text, accidentally hits escape\"}],[{\"lit\":\"ShipReq stores text in local storage and closes without a prompt.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"User re-opens editor, we initialise it with the previous draft value.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Something like that. There'd be a bunch of considerations to make though...\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"How do they discard the draft themselves. Being able to revert your edits (esp deletes) is essential.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Might be an idea to look to gmail and it's draft management for this (and for established UX)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Need to consider cases where the original is updated after the draft. How to merge?\"}]]}]}}}",
    "{\"#\":885,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:28:13.140131Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqImplicationsPatch\":{\"dir\":\"<-\",\"id\":{\"gr\":135},\"patch\":{\"+\":[{\"gr\":57}],\"-\":[]}}}}",
    "{\"#\":886,\"createdAt\":\"2020-08-19T00:30:13.779174Z\",\"event\":{\"ReqFieldCustomTextSet\":{\"fid\":1,\"id\":{\"gr\":135},\"value\":[{\"web\":\"https://twitter.com/olafurpg/status/1295766220369788929\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"> I pressed escape and Jira just discarded my comment that I had been drafting for 30 minutes\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"> I wonder if there’s an extension that stores all text inputs in local storage for recovery. It’s hard to know in advance when you’re about to start drafting a long response.\"},{\"bl\":{}},{\"lit\":\"We should do better. Maybe drafts should be stored in local storage until committed. In fact, what about this:\"},{\"ol\":[[{\"lit\":\"User writes lots of text, accidentally hits escape\"}],[{\"lit\":\"ShipReq stores text in local storage and closes without a prompt.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"User re-opens editor, we initialise it with the previous draft value.\"}]]},{\"lit\":\"Something like that. There'd be a bunch of considerations to make though...\"},{\"ul\":[[{\"lit\":\"How do they discard the draft themselves. Being able to revert your edits (esp deletes) is essential.\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Might be an idea to look to gmail and it's draft management for this (and for established UX)\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Need to consider cases where the original is updated after the draft. How to merge?\"}],[{\"lit\":\"Safety concerns around local storage. Also portability concerns. Maybe best to store all drafts on server-side: better security, more useful, once a draft UI is included users will expect it everywhere anyway. (like gmail)\"}]]}]}}}",
